&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;US EST time-zone (NYC preferred)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We regret that we are unable to provide work visa sponsorship at this time.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cutover provides enterprise technology operations teams with an AI-powered SaaS solution that automates and streamlines complex processes with intelligent runbooks. The Cutover solution enables teams to respond to incidents quickly, recover from IT outages, and manage cloud migrations with precision and efficiency. Cutover is used in many of the world’s largest financial institutions to support their critical technology operations, including 5 out of the top 6 largest asset managers and 3 out of the top 5 US banks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What does this role mean to us?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a versatile, hands-on Marketing Manager to drive pipeline and brand awareness across the full marketing mix. This isn’t a narrow specialist role; you’ll move confidently between field events, digital demand generation, technical content, and social, while working closely with sales, product, and partners to grow our presence in large enterprise verticals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you be doing as our Marketing Manager?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field &amp;amp; partner marketing — Plan and execute executive dinners, roundtables, webinars, conference sponsorships, and partner co-marketing (e.g. AWS), owning logistics and reporting against pipeline targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Digital demand generation — Build, optimise, and report on paid campaigns across LinkedIn, Meta, YouTube, and other B2B channels; support SEO and landing page best practices to drive qualified leads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical content &amp;amp; storytelling — Translate complex IT operations topics (disaster recovery, incident management, cloud migration) into clear, compelling content — blogs, guides, white papers, and landing pages — for CTOs, SREs, and DevOps audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Social media — Own Cutover’s organic social strategy and brand voice (LinkedIn primary), building a content calendar and growing engaged community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage AI — Integrate LLMs and emerging AI tools into content production, personalisation, and marketing automation to move faster and scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate &amp;amp; report — Partner with sales, product, revenue ops, and leadership to align on campaigns and measure what’s working.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we’d like you to bring to the table…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of B2B marketing experience, ideally in SaaS or enterprise tech (financial services a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on track record running field events end-to-end and managing paid and/or social campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong writer who can make technical topics clear and engaging without losing accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable owning programs in a fast-moving, lean team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent with HubSpot, Google Analytics, LinkedIn Campaign Manager, and AI-powered marketing tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Salesforce, SEO tools, and ABM is a bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
